that requires a high degree of interpretation. How the inherent complexity of \
textual data arises from its dependence on interpretation, context, and \
linguistic nuance, which makes its processing particularly challenging in \
academic research.</p><p>Emilio Munoz will present his work on Order-Aware \
State Representations for Path-Dependent Reinforcement Learning, exploring \
how we might design compact state representations that preserve chronological \
order while still being computationally feasible.</p><p>Phileas Dazeley-Gaist \
will discuss their ongoing work with the 2025 CGS Sympoietic Art Organism \
group. The talk will showcase a citation network grown by a small artist \
community in intentional collaboration working from a shared commons. Over a \
series of co-creative cycles, artists iteratively remix and take inspiration \
from works already in the commons, contributing new pieces while tracking \
citation relationships.</p>\>\""}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"\"\<speakers\>\"", "\[Rule]", 
         RowBox[{"{", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"\[LeftAssociation]", 
            RowBox[{
             
             RowBox[{"\"\<name\>\"", 
